{"lemma":"إِزالَةُ","slug":"إِزالَةُ","root":"ز.#.ل","root_slug":"ز-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18421","n18527"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of أَزَالَ (ʔazāla) (form IV)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"removal"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of أَزَالَ (ʔazāla)."},"ipa":["/ʔi.zaː.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18421","headword_ar":"ازالهُ","root":"zwl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAlapN","text_ar":"اـِزَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zw~lhu","text_ar":"زوّلهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazowiylN","text_ar":"تَزْوِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AizodaAlahu","text_ar":"اِزْدَالَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AizotaAlahu","text_ar":"اِزْتَالَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AizodiyaAlN","text_ar":"اِزْدِيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,) this being syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAlapN","text_ar":"اـِزَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed it; made it to go away, pass away, depart, remove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shift;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA;) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it to cease to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exist,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to come to nought: did away with it; annulled it: effaced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obliterated, it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zilotuhu","text_ar":"زِلْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azaAluhu","text_ar":"اَزَالُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aziyluhu","text_ar":"اَزِيلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which see in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zyl","text_ar":"زيل"},{"kind":"text","text":",] signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azalotuhu","text_ar":"اَزَلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaw~alotuhu","text_ar":"زَوَّلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AzAlhu Eani AlmawoDiEi","text_ar":"ازالهُ عَنِ المَوْضِعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed it from the place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA: and the like is said in the K.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AzAl Eanohu ka*aA","text_ar":"ازال عَنْهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed from him such a thing; made it to go away, pass away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cease, from him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to leave him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit him; he freed him from it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rid him of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AzAlhu En raA^oyihi","text_ar":"ازالهُ عن رَاْيِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, made him to turn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swerve, from his opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sentiment."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AzAl A@ll~`hu zawaAlahu","text_ar":"ازال ا@للّٰهُ زَوَالَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawaAlahaA","text_ar":"زَوَالَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawaAlN","text_ar":"زَوَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". [See also 4 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zyl","text_ar":"زيل"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n18527","headword_ar":"ازالهُ","root":"zyl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino makaAnihi","text_ar":"مِنْ مَكَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano makaAnihi","text_ar":"عَنْ مَكَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAlapN","text_ar":"اـِزَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAlN","text_ar":"اـِزَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAlahu","text_ar":"زَالَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, and Har p. 393,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaziyluhu","text_ar":"يَزِيلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, and Har ubi suprà,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yazaAluhu","text_ar":"يَزَالُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanaAluhu","text_ar":"يَنَالُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayolN","text_ar":"زَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, Har,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziyaAlN","text_ar":"زِيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) both signify the same; (S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed it"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the former is expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zwl","text_ar":"زول"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb in explanation of both, and Har ubi suprà in explanation of the latter;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAyalahu","text_ar":"زَايَلَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the primary signification is that first assigned to it in the next preceding paragraph. (Har ubi suprà.) See also 1, fourth sentence. [And see 4 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zwl","text_ar":"زول"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Har"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}